('GitHub Copilot','AI pair programmer that suggests code completions and entire functions in your IDE.','GitHub Copilot is an AI coding assistant powered by OpenAI Codex. It integrates into VS Code, JetBrains IDEs, Neovim, and more, providing inline code suggestions, whole-function completions, and chat assistance. Copilot X expands this with pull request summaries, docs generation, and CLI assistance.','Code',ARRAY['coding','IDE','autocomplete','GitHub','VS Code','pair programming'],'Paid',10.00,'https://github.com/features/copilot','https://github.githubassets.com/images/modules/site/copilot/copilot.png',2021,'GitHub (Microsoft)',true,3876,'US',47.6062,-122.3321),

('Cursor','The AI-first code editor built on VS Code with deep codebase understanding and multi-file editing.','Cursor is an AI-powered fork of VS Code designed for AI-assisted software development. It features Cmd+K for inline edits, a chat interface with codebase context (@codebase), multi-file editing (Composer), and uses frontier models (Claude, GPT-4). Cursor understands entire codebases, can apply diffs across files, and dramatically speeds up development.','Code',ARRAY['coding','IDE','VS Code','multi-file','codebase','editor'],'Freemium',20.00,'https://cursor.sh','https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/126759922',2022,'Anysphere',true,4540,'US',37.7749,-122.4194),

